The paper discusses the development of a research environment for the analysis of structured and unstructured data using text mining methods, which falls under the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), deep learning (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and cybernetics (cs.CY). The use of notebooks for executable script documents also suggests a focus on computational methods and tools, further supporting these sub-categories.
